@deffn Function gdk-event-get-state  (self@tie{}@code{<gdk-event>}) (state@tie{}@code{<gdk-modifier-type*>}) @result{}@tie{} (ret@tie{}@code{bool})
If the event contains a "state" field, puts that field in @var{state}. Otherwise
stores an empty state (0). Returns @samp{@code{#t}} if there was a state field
in the event. @var{event} may be @samp{@code{#f}}, in which case it's treated as
if the event had no state field.

@table @var
@item event
a @code{<gdk-event>} or NULL

@item state
return location for state

@item ret
@samp{@code{#t}} if there was a state field in the event

@end table

@end deffn

