@deffn Function gdk-event-handler-set  (func@tie{}@code{<gdk-event-func>}) (data@tie{}@code{<gpointer>}) (notify@tie{}@code{<g-destroy-notify>})
Sets the function to call to handle all events from GDK.

Note that GTK+ uses this to install its own event handler, so it is usually not
useful for GTK+ applications. (Although an application can call this function
then call @code{gtk-main-do-event} to pass events to GTK+.)

@table @var
@item func
the function to call to handle events from GDK.

@item data
user data to pass to the function.

@item notify
the function to call when the handler function is removed, i.e. when
@code{gdk-event-handler-set} is called with another event handler.

@end table

@end deffn

